article.story: BANGOR, Maine -- — Peter Filipovity had 23 points in Maine's 81-73 victory over Albany on Thursday night. Filipovity also contributed 11 rebounds for the Black Bears (10-10, 2/3 America East Conference). Kristians Feierbergs scored 16 points while going 6 of 10 (4 for 5 from 3-point range), and added five rebounds. Kellen Tynes shot 5 of 12 from the field and 5 for 10 from the line to finish with 15 points. Sebastian Thomas led the way for the Great Danes (10-10, 2-3) with 20 points, four assists, two steals and two blocks. Amar'e Marshall added 15 points for Albany. Jonathan Beagle also had 14 points, 13 rebounds and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
